        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> This specifies the total number of recurring periods from the recurring date to the end of the product service lifecycle.  TOTAL_RECUR_PERIODS (Type: Integer, Length: 10) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s65"><Data ss:Type="String">Period Precision Base Unit</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> The base time unit used as a starting point for all calculations.  FK_UNT_BASE_PERIOD_ID (Type: String, Length: 15) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s64"><Data ss:Type="String">Rounding</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> For rates that are period based and the charge covers a period of time that is not an exact multiple of the rate period.  This value identifies the rule used to process the remainder - Options: P(Pro-rata), R(Round), U(Round Up), D(Round Down).  PERIOD_ROUND_RULE (Type: String, Length: 1) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s64"><Data ss:Type="String">Rate Plan Selection</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> Identifies how the rating process for the Charge obtains the effective rate for this product.  Options: STATIC, DYNAMIC, AD-HOC.  PRODUCT_RATE_CONTROL (Type: String, Length: 10) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s64"><Data ss:Type="String">MPCM - Rate</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> Monthly Period Conversion Method(MPCM) indicator for Rate period.  Options: C(Calendar), T(Unit Conversion).  PERIOD_CONVERSION_RATE (Type: String, Length: 1) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s64"><Data ss:Type="String">MPCM - Full Charge</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> Monthly Period Conversion Method(MPCM) indicator for Full Charge period. Options: C(Calendar), T(Unit Conversion).  PERIOD_CONVERSION_FULL_CRG (Type: String, Length: 1) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s64"><Data ss:Type="String">MPCM - Partial Charge</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> Monthly Period Conversion Method(MPCM) indicator for Partial Charge period. Options: C(Calendar), T(Unit Conversion).  PERIOD_CONVERSION_PARTIAL_CRG (Type: String, Length: 1) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s64"><Data ss:Type="String">Charge Rate Date Indicator</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> Defines the method of determining the date by which the charge will be available for rating. Options:S(Start Date),E(End Date),D(Specified Date).  RATING_DATE_IND (Type: String, Length: 1) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s64"><Data ss:Type="String">Charge Rate Date Offset Multiplier</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> Defines the offset for the charge rate date calculation.  RATING_DATE_NUM (Type: Integer, Length: 10) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s65"><Data ss:Type="String">Charge Rate Date Offset Unit</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> This unit is used in conjunction with offset multiplier to determine the charge rating date offset.  FK_UNT_RATING_ID (Type: String, Length: 15) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s65"><Data ss:Type="String">Charge Rate Date</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> Specific date by when the charge becomes available for rating.  RATE_DATE (Type: Date) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s64"><Data ss:Type="String">Charge Billing Date Indicator</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> Defines the method of determining the date by which the charge will be available for posting to the billing period. Options:S(Start Date),E(End Date),D(Specified Date).  BLP_INCL_DATE_IND (Type: String, Length: 1) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s64"><Data ss:Type="String">Charge Billing Date Offset Multiplier</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> Defines the offset for the charge billing period inclusion date calculation.  BLP_INCL_DATE_NUM (Type: Integer, Length: 10) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s65"><Data ss:Type="String">Charge Billing Date Offset Unit</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> This unit is used in conjunction with offset multiplier to determine the charge billing inclusion date offset.  FK_UNT_BLP_INCL_ID (Type: String, Length: 15) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s65"><Data ss:Type="String">Charge Billing Date</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> Specific date by when the charge becomes available to be posted into the billing period.  BLP_INCL_DATE (Type: Date) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s65"><Data ss:Type="String">Discount Type</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> Indicates what kind of discount will be applied. Options:  Percentage(%), Amount(AMT).  DISCOUNT_TYPE (Type: String, Length: 3) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s65"><Data ss:Type="String">Discount</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> The discount percentage or amount to be applied to the Charge.  DISCOUNT_AMOUNT (Type: Numeric, Length: 18, 6) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s64"><Data ss:Type="String">Minimum Value Indicator</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> Determines if the product rating plan minimum value per charge should be enforced for this product service and if so - how it is enforced. Options: YES(Apply Rating Plan), NO(Do Not Apply), OVR(Apply Override).  APPLY_MIN_IND (Type: String, Length: 3) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s65"><Data ss:Type="String">Min Override Value</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> Minimum override value.  MIN_OVERRIDE_VALUE (Type: Numeric, Length: 18, 6) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s64"><Data ss:Type="String">Maximum Value Indicator</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> Determines if the product rating plan minimum value per charge should be enforced for this product service and if so - how it is enforced. Options: YES(Apply Rating Plan), NO(Do Not Apply), OVR(Apply Override).  APPLY_MAX_IND (Type: String, Length: 3) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s65"><Data ss:Type="String">Max Override Value</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> Maximum override value.  MAX_OVERRIDE_VALUE (Type: Numeric, Length: 18, 6) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s64"><Data ss:Type="String">% Shared</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> The percentage apportioned to the billable party in this product service when charges are shared.  SPLIT_PERCENTAGE (Type: Numeric, Length: 5, 2) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s65"><Data ss:Type="String">Shared Charge Reference</Data><Comment
      ss:Author="hercules"><ss:Data xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><Font
        html:Face="Arial" x:Family="Swiss"> Stores a reference to enable charges that are split between multiple billable parties to be referenced to each other.  SPLIT_REFERENCE (Type: String, Length: 30) </Font></ss:Data></Comment></Cell>
   </Row>
';
        DBMS_LOB.APPEND(p_xml, v_header);
    END "GENERATE_TEMPLATE_CLOB";

